document_title: Foreskin inflammation: Causes, signs and prevention
subsection_content: Doctors often review medical history and examine the patient's health. In some cases, pus can be removed from the glans to determine whether the cause is bacterial or fungal. In addition, the doctor may also order a blood test if the man has serious diseases such as diabetes or syphilis.
